Yusuf Dantalle has emerged governorship candidate of the Allied Peoples Movement (APM) for the November 16 election in Kogi State. Chairman of the electoral panel, who doubles as the National Secretary of the party, Mr Ayodele Oyadeyi, declared Dantalle as the party’s candidate following a unanimous affirmation by all the 120 delegates from the 21 LGAs present at event in Lokoja. In his acceptance speech, the APM flagbearer, Dantalle, while thanking the delegates for the confidence reposed in him, assured them that he would provide accountable leadership through constant engagement with citizens and stakeholders in delivering services and promoting policies that would encourage sustainable livelihood through partnership, if elected. We’ll resist APC’s move to frustrate our petition — APM chair APM rejects reconstituted Ogun Tribunal, indicts Osinbajo, Tinubu Buhari clears air on Ogun governorship tussle, endorses Abiodun OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY